{"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/SocketProtocol"]]},"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/SocketProtocol\/set(keepalive:)"},"kind":"symbol","variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/gio\/socketprotocol\/set(keepalive:)"]}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"patch":0,"minor":3},"metadata":{"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"set","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"text":"keepalive","kind":"externalParam"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"text":"Bool","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb"},{"kind":"text","text":")"}],"roleHeading":"Instance Method","role":"symbol","title":"set(keepalive:)","symbolKind":"method","modules":[{"name":"GIO"}],"externalID":"s:3GIO14SocketProtocolPAAE3set9keepaliveySb_tF","extendedModule":"GIO"},"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"set"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"keepalive"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb","text":"Bool","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"kind":"text","text":")"}]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"discussion","type":"heading","text":"Discussion","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This option is only functional on certain kinds of sockets. (Notably,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"tcp"},{"type":"text","text":" sockets.)"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The exact time between pings is system- and protocol-dependent, but will","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"normally be at least two hours. Most commonly, you would set this flag","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"on a server socket if you want to allow clients to remain idle for long"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"periods of time, but also want to ensure that connections are eventually"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"garbage-collected if clients crash or become unreachable."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Sets or unsets the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"SO_KEEPALIVE"},{"type":"text","text":" flag on the underlying socket. When"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"this flag is set on a socket, the system will attempt to verify that the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"remote socket endpoint is still present if a sufficiently long period of","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"time passes with no data being exchanged. If the system is unable to"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"verify the presence of the remote endpoint, it will automatically close"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"the connection.","type":"text"}],"sections":[],"references":{"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/SocketProtocol":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/SocketProtocol","title":"SocketProtocol","url":"\/documentation\/gio\/socketprotocol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A "},{"code":"GSocket","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" is a low-level networking primitive. It is a more or less"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"direct mapping of the BSD socket API in a portable GObject based API.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"It supports both the UNIX socket implementations and winsock2 on Windows.","type":"text"}],"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"protocol"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"SocketProtocol","kind":"identifier"}],"kind":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"SocketProtocol","kind":"identifier"}],"role":"symbol","type":"topic"},"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO":{"type":"topic","abstract":[],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO","title":"GIO","url":"\/documentation\/gio","role":"collection","kind":"symbol"},"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/SocketProtocol/set(keepalive:)":{"role":"symbol","kind":"symbol","title":"set(keepalive:)","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/SocketProtocol\/set(keepalive:)","url":"\/documentation\/gio\/socketprotocol\/set(keepalive:)","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Sets or unsets the "},{"code":"SO_KEEPALIVE","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" flag on the underlying socket. When","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"this flag is set on a socket, the system will attempt to verify that the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"remote socket endpoint is still present if a sufficiently long period of","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"time passes with no data being exchanged. If the system is unable to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"verify the presence of the remote endpoint, it will automatically close"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"the connection."}],"fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"set"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"keepalive"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb","text":"Bool"},{"kind":"text","text":")"}]}}}